Total line count: Total lines in the files, including empty lines and comments
Lines of code: Used sonarqube value as it is most correct, ck can have a margin of error due to the intermediate representation used, jk computes the sum of all code lines in methods
statement count: The total count of statements in the project
Cyclomatic complexity: Used CK value as it takes more decision points into account
Average Cyclomatic complexity for method: This describes the average cyclomatic complexity for methods, rather than the whole project
Average lines of code for methods: Shows the average lines of code for all methods
Average lines of code for methods with a: This is included as it excludes methods like simple getters and setters
Coupling between objects: Describes the total number of dependencies classes have. This is the same as ck_fanout
Dependencies in: Describes the total number of dependencies on classes of the project. This is the same as cboModified-fanout
Number of Children: The sum of the immediate children every class has through inheritance
Response for a class: The sum of unique method invocations for each class
Cohesion Among Methods of Classes: The mean of the CAMC metric
Lack of Cohesion in Methods 5: The mean of the LCOM5 metric, JPeek was used here because it uses a newer version of the algorithm then CK does, CK themself says that the version they use it unreliable
Method-Method through Attributes Cohesio: The mean of the MMAC metric
Normalized Hamming Distance: The mean of the NHD metric
A Sensitive Metric of Class Cohesion: The mean of the SCOM metric
Tight Class Cohesion: The mean of the tight class cohesion value, describing cohesion of the project through method invocations
Loose Class Cohesion: The mean of the loose class cohesion value, similair to tcc, but restricting which methods to include more.
Third party classes used: Shows how many third party classes are used, such as the java API and other libraries
Third party methods used: Shows how many third party methods are used, such as the java API and other libraries
